**What does a Director of Reconstruction with Paul Davis do?**  

* Serve your community when it needs it the most;
* Provide leadership and guidance to the reconstruction project managers
* Oversee and direct construction projects from conception to completion
* Direct, mentor and support direct reports through training and feedback
* Celebrate completion of projects with a team of skilled tradespeople, homeowners grateful to be back in their homes, and your Paul Davis team members;
* Have fun and be part of a growing business!

The Director of reconstruction is responsible and accountable for overseeing all jobs from start to finish. This position will ensure all reconstruction activities are in compliance with project scope, budget and metrics. This position will work very closely with the reconstruction project managers and compliance department, to make sure all projects are within budget and being managed efficiently.




**Why The Team Needs You?** Serving others in their time of need is not easy. We will need you to build foundational relationships based on trust, actively listen, and find ways to manage a team to complete projects successfully. We also want a fun personality that enjoys getting results and helping people. Are you a fast-paced problem solver? Do you enjoy managing and guiding a team to achieve success? If so, this position is for you.  



