* Meet operational objectives of: Sales, Gross Margin, Brand Experience, etc.;
* Profitably scope, estimate, and sign projects to get started, then create work orders and manage the entire execution of the project while managing your own budget;
* Ensure compliance with regulations, standards, and service level agreements;
* Build relationships with insurance professionals, TPAs, and customers (direct and B2B);
* Recruit, develop, and manage subcontractors/tradesmen; develop partnerships and improve team performance.
* Manage & train the reconstruction team including conducting weekly meetings
* Maintain adjuster/company relationships

**Compensation and Benefits:**  



* Compensation Range: $80k to >$120k, consisting of a combination of base salary, stipends, year-end bonus, performance-based bonus, and/or profit-sharing.
* Health insurance (medical, dental, and vision coverage offered), disability insurance, and HSA.
* 401(k) with company matching.
* PTO, sick days, and paid holidays.
* Generous monthly cell phone allowance, car allowance, gas and toll reimbursements, etc.




